Then, compute the sum of all such \( x \). ### Key Steps: 1. **Identify Relationships:** - \(\tan x = \frac{\sin x}{\cos x}\) - \(\cot x = \frac{1}{\tan x}\) - \(\tan x = \cot x\) when \(\tan x = \pm 1\), i.e., \(x = 45^\circ, 135^\circ, 225^\circ, 315^\circ\). 2. **Analyze Each Case:** - **Case 1:** \(x = 135^\circ\) - \(\sin 135^\circ = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\) - \(\cos 135^\circ = -\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\) - \(\tan 135^\circ = -1\) - \(\cot 135^\circ = -1\) - Distinct values: \(\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}, -\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}, -1\) (three values). - **Case 2:** \(x = 315^\circ\) - \
